.TH "acpi_dev_get_first_match_dev" 9 "acpi_dev_get_first_match_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_dev_get_first_match_dev \- Return the first match of ACPI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct acpi_device *" acpi_dev_get_first_match_dev
.BI "(const char *hid "  ","
.BI "const char *uid "  ","
.BI "s64 hrv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hid" 12
Hardware ID of the device.
.IP "uid" 12
Unique ID of the device, pass NULL to not check _UID
.IP "hrv" 12
Hardware Revision of the device, pass -1 to not check _HRV
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the first match of ACPI device if a matching device was present
at the moment of invocation, or NULL otherwise.

The caller is responsible to call \fBput_device\fP on the returned device.

See additional information in \fBacpi_dev_present\fP as well.
